=== START T-05 socket.on('end')ハンドラ追加 (2026-02-08 20:12:46) ===
Commit successful.

**Summary of T-05:**

Added a `socket.on('end')` event handler in `unity-mcp-ts/src/core/UnityConnection.ts:97-101` to detect half-open TCP connections. When the Unity C# side sends a FIN packet (graceful shutdown), the `end` event fires, we log it, and call `socket.destroy()` to fully close the socket. This triggers the existing `close` handler which performs cleanup (removing from `clients`, `clientDataBuffers`, `clientInfoMap` maps and updating `activeClientId`).
Note: Test/build commands were not approved for execution. The change is minimal and syntactically verified by reading the surrounding code.


